</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uamaeliya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaeliya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 3:57:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2210.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Kizdean Gix and Fire Beetles</span><hr size=1> Gix.  Without doubt.  Back RL months and months ago, when I was about level 12 or so, I healed my Druid and Bard friends (the Bard had a personal grudge against Gix) while they fought the teir'dal.  We won, the Bard was happy, the Druid was happy, I was happy, Gix was not.<br>
<br>
He got his damn revenge for that.<br>
<br>
I hate the phrase &quot;revenge is a dish best served cold&quot; because it makes so much sense.  As a side note, I'm in my 30th season now.  Gix cons light blue to me.  In any case, last week, I signed on in the Commonlands and checked for tracks as a habit.  Well, what do you know!  Gix has been by recently. I thought I'd kill him again, for old time's sake.  He hardly seemed like a fight at all.  So, I set off, put on my trusty DS and have all the right spells up for when I go hunt later.  I Snare him, and start to nuke.  He comes in, and just works on punching me.<br>
<br>
LOADING PLEASE WAIT...<br>
<br>
I'm astounded.  I would have had NO problem killing this damn thing!  Even though I timed my spells the way I always do (and they go off without a hitch the majority of the time), for some reason my timing was off and Gix kept interrupting my spells!  Despite my beloved &quot;Fluffy&quot; (does 20 damage a hit on average) I didn't have a chance only meleeing.<br>
<br>
I stormed back to my corpse, found it after oh, six or seven minutes, looted it, and had Gix back up on track.  I wanted him bloody dead.  I track him...  only to find that a half elf, or maybe a human, too-talls look a lot alike, and an ogre beating up on Gix.  <br>
<br>
Gix, from what I could tell, was beating them.  As much as I wanted to kill Gix myself, they had beaten me to it.  I healed the human/half-elf up, buffed him, DSed him, and sat down to wait for Gix to die.  The human/half-elf, apparently not realizing that he was no longer on the verge of death, ran to one of the nearby guards, who ignored Gix.  Gix eventually died, and the human/half-elf runs off without a word to me (he thanked me later, though).<br>
<br>
So, because of that, Gix has made number one on my MUST-DIE list.  If I'm in the Commonlands and see him, I'm tracking and slaughtering him.<br>
<br>
Yeah, that's a pet peeve of mine.<br>
<br>
Oh, fire beetles.  Nothing major here, I just hate how the damn things gang up on you.  The absolute BANE of my existance when I was but a youngin' with the clip turned down so low I could hardly see the path (much less the cave to the guards) in the daytime.  I've lost track of the number of times I could finally handle one and just got killed by another that started working on me as well.  This was also, by the way, before I learned the merits of con'ing a creature before attacking it.  I've learned a lot since those days, but they are by no means forgotten.<br>
<br>
If you ever see Gix, kill him as a personal favor to me, to yourself, and to Norrath in general.<br>
<br>
<br>
Amaeliya Sylvanheart<br>
Druidess Halfling of the 30th Circle of Karana<br>
Halfheight Heroes<br>
